    The crash is caused by an off-by-one read in crc8().                        
                                                                                
    In main():                                                                  
                                                                                
                                                                                
     uint8_t buf[7] = {0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x05, 0x06, 0x07};               
     uint8_t c = crc8(buf, sizeof(buf));                                        
                                                                                
                                                                                
    buf is a stack array with exactly 7 bytes. Its valid indexes are:           
                                                                                
                                                                                
     buf[0] ... buf[6]                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    sizeof(buf) is 7, so crc8() is called as:                                   
                                                                                
                                                                                
     crc8(buf, 7)                                                               
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Inside crc8():                                                              
                                                                                
                                                                                
     for (size_t i = 0; i <= len; i++) {                                        
         crc ^= buf[i];                                                         
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Because the loop condition is i <= len, the loop runs for:                  
                                                                                
                                                                                
     i = 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7                                                 
                                                                                
                                                                                
    The first seven iterations, i = 0 through i = 6, are valid and read the     
    initialized bytes of buf.                                                   
                                                                                
    On the final iteration:                                                     
                                                                                
                                                                                
     i == 7                                                                     
     len == 7                                                                   
                                                                                
                                                                                
    The condition i <= len is still true, so the program executes:              
                                                                                
                                                                                
     crc ^= buf[7];                                                             
                                                                                
                                                                                
    But buf[7] is one byte past the end of the stack array. AddressSanitizer    
    detects that one-byte out-of-bounds read and reports:                       
                                                                                
                                                                                
     Stack buffer overflow                                                      
                                                                                
                                                                                
    The variable c in main() is never successfully assigned because the crash   
    happens inside crc8() before it returns.                                    
                                                                                
    The CRC computation itself is not the problem; the bug is that len is       
    being treated inconsistently. len is passed as a byte count, but the loop   
    treats it like the last valid index. For a buffer of length 7, the last     
    valid index is 6, not 7.                                                    
                                                                                
    Recommendation                                                              
                                                                                
    In                                                                          
    /Users/ibraheemamin/projects/COS484/chatdbgpro/bench/cases/off-by-one-crcÔÇª  
    line 11, change the loop condition from inclusive to exclusive:             
                                                                                
                                                                                
     for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++) {                                         
                                                                                
                                                                                
    So the fixed function should be:                                            
                                                                                
                                                                                
     static uint8_t crc8(const uint8_t *buf, size_t len) {                      
         uint8_t crc = 0x00;                                                    
                                                                                
         for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++) {                                     
             crc ^= buf[i];                                                     
             for (int b = 0; b < 8; b++) {                                      
                 crc = (crc & 0x80)                                             
                     ? (uint8_t)((crc << 1) ^ 0x07)                             
                     : (uint8_t)(crc << 1);                                     
             }                                                                  
         }                                                                      
                                                                                
         return crc;                                                            
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Minimal local fix: replace i <= len with i < len.                           
                                                                                
    More thorough root-cause fix: document and enforce that len is a byte       
    count, not a final index. For example:                                      
                                                                                
                                                                                
     /* Computes CRC-8 over exactly len bytes: buf[0] through buf[len - 1].     
     */                                                                         
     static uint8_t crc8(const uint8_t *buf, size_t len) {                      
         ...                                                                    
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    The call site in main() is already correct:                                 
                                                                                
                                                                                
     uint8_t c = crc8(buf, sizeof(buf));                                        
                                                                                
                                                                                
    The defect is entirely in the loop bound inside crc8().                     
                                                                                
